The paper presents a neural network model that learns to solve SAT problems from single bit supervision. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves training a machine learning model to perform a task. The model uses message passing techniques, which are commonly used in graph neural networks, and thus it could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of random graphs and graph coloring, clique detection, dominating set, and vertex cover problems, which are all related to graph theory and algorithms, and thus it could be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the use of small random graphs, which could also be related to computer vision (cs.CV) as graphs are often used to represent images.
